<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>They've been keeping a low profile since the start of the coronavirus pandemic and haven't been seen in public for almost six months.</p>

<p>But Jennifer Lawrence and her husband Cooke Maroney, 36, continued a string of recent sightings on Saturday as they took a relaxing stroll through Manhattan's SoHo neighborhood.</p>

<p>The 30-year-old Oscar winner had all eyes on her thanks to her vibrant green dress. </p>

<p>Loved-up couple: Jennifer Lawrence, 30, was spotted out in Manhattan's SoHo neighborhood with her husband Cooke Maroney, 36, as they walked hand-in-hand to lunch</p>

<p>Jennifer's short dress was dotted with figures of dancing people and showcased her toned legs.</p>

<p>She wore the spaghetti-strap item with simple white trainers while carrying a slim mauve–pink suede handbag.</p>

<p>She blocked out the sun with reflective cat-eye sunglasses and wore her blonde tresses parted down the middle.</p>

<p>Cooke was more casually dressed with a white T-shirt featuring the classic 'America Online' logo from AOL. </p>

<p>Seeing green: Jennifer had all eyes on her thanks to her vibrant green dress that was dotted with figures of dancing people and showcased her toned legs</p>

<p>The art gallery director wore navy blue trousers and a pair of gray trainers while rocking a silver luxury wristwatch and black wayfarers.</p>

<p>Jennifer and Cooke had their hands tightly clasped as the walked down the street together as they headed to lunch.</p>

<p>Both wore pale blue surgical masks to do their part to help slow the spread of the novel coronavirus.</p>

<p>The Silver Linings Playbook actress began dating Cooke in 2018, following the dissolution a year earlier of her relationship with director Darren Aronofsky.</p>

<p>The couple got engaged in February of last year, and they tied the knot in October 2019 in Rhode Island.</p>

<p>Low key: The art gallery director wore navy blue trousers and a pair of gray trainers while rocking a silver luxury wristwatch and black wayfarers</p>

<p>Off the radar: The couple haven't been seen in public for almost six months, around when the pandemic began</p>

<p>Though she released multiple films per year while filming at the height of her career, in recent years Jennifer has slowed her paced and only released a single film per year.</p>

<p>Most recently, she reprised her role as Mystique for a small performance in last year's critically derided X-Men film Dark Phoenix, and prior to that she appeared in the spy thriller Red Sparrow (2018) and the psychological horror film Mother! (2017), which was directed by Aronofsky.</p>

<p>Although the pandemic has shut down much of Hollywood the actress has some major projects in the works once filming can resume.</p>

<p>Moved on: Jenifer began dating Cooke in 2018, following the dissolution of her relationship with Darren Aronofsky, who directed her in 2017's Mother!; pictured in 2017</p>

<p>She's set to star in Red, White And Water, an upcoming drama helmed by theatre director Lila Neugebauer that also star's Atlanta Bryan Tyree Henry and Orange Is The New Black's Samira Wiley, for which she's already completed shooting.</p>

<p>She has two upcoming projects with The Big Short director Adam McKay, including Bad Blood, in which she'll star as disgraced Theranos founder Elizabeth Holmes, and Don't Look Up, in which she and Cate Blanchett with play astronomers trying to warn everyone on Earth that a massive asteroid will crash into the planet in sixth months.</p>

<p>Jennifer will also play the lead in acclaimed Italian director Paolo Sorrentino's next feature, Mob Girl. </p>

<p>Coming up: She's only released one film per year in recent years, but Jennifer has multiple new projects cued up, including two comic releases from The Big Short's Adam McKay; shown in June 2019</p>
